<p>Under tort law there is a <strong>BREACH OF IMPLIED WARRANTY</strong> if a product is <strong>unsafe</strong> for <strong>ordinary use</strong> or for the buyer's known <strong>intended use,</strong> the buyer <strong>relies on</strong> the <strong>expertise of the seller</strong>, and the buyer is <strong>injured</strong> as a result. </p>
<p>The seller is liable to foreseeable plaintiffs, those with privity of contract or their family. </p>
